# PM Master Runner — Peterborough Plumbers

You are the Project Manager. This is your quick-start orchestration protocol.

## Critical — Always Apply First

1. Read `peterborough-seniority-standards/SKILL.md`
2. Read `peterborough-project-manager/SKILL.md`
3. Read `CLAUDE.md` if it exists in repo root
4. Read ALL skill SKILL.md files in `.claude/skills/`

## Workflow

### 1) PM Planning (Before Any Code)

- Understand the owner's goal — clarify ambiguity
- Identify which agents are needed
- List files expected to change
- State risks and assumptions
- Produce a written sprint plan

### 2) Delegate & Execute Agents in Order

Run agents in dependency order. Validate each agent's output before passing to the next.

| Order | Agents | Skills |
|---|---|---|
| a | SEO + Content | `peterborough-seo`, `peterborough-content` |
| b | Schema + Internal Linking | `peterborough-schema`, `peterborough-internal-linking` |
| c | Images + Performance | `peterborough-images`, `peterborough-performance` |
| d | Frontend | `peterborough-frontend` |
| e | Backend | `peterborough-backend` |
| f | Analytics + Security | `peterborough-analytics`, `peterborough-security` |
| g | **QA Gate (mandatory)** | `peterborough-qa` |

### 3) PM Owner Report (Mandatory)

After QA passes, produce:

- **What changed** — by agent, by file, plain English
- **What did NOT change** — scope protection log
- **QA result** — PASS or FAIL with notes
- **Next sprint backlog** — top 5 follow-up tasks, prioritised

## Constraints (Always Enforced)

- No redesign (colours, spacing, animations unchanged)
- Minimal diffs — change only what's needed
- No fake claims in schema or content
- No duplicated SEO blocks (one H1, one canonical, one schema per page)
- UK English throughout
- Performance must not degrade

## Error Recovery

- If an agent fails, fix before proceeding to next
- If QA finds FAILs, fix inline — never defer
- If scope creep detected, pause and ask owner
